@node Main Features
@section Main Features
@itemize
@item
@strong{Text-to-Speech:} Reads any buffer aloud using different
backends.
@item
@strong{Synchronized Reading:} The cursor moves along with the text
being read.
@item
@strong{Multiple Backends:} Supports @code{espeak},
@code{speech-dispatcher}, @code{piper} and macOS's native speech
synthesis.
@item
@strong{Continuous Mode:} Automatically advances to the next page or
section in multi-page modes like @code{info-mode} or @code{nov-mode}.
@item
@strong{Timer:} Set a timer to read for a specific duration.
@item
@strong{On-the-fly Translation:} Translate and read buffers in different
languages.
@item
@strong{Audiobook Creation:} Convert any buffer into an audiobook.
@item
@strong{Enriched Text:} Announce links and other clickable elements in
the buffer.
@item
@strong{Custom Pronunciation:} Define custom pronunciation rules using
dictionaries.
@item
@strong{Study Mode:} Repeatedly read a buffer or a region for study
purposes.
@item
@strong{Estimated Reading Time:} Shows the estimated reading time in the
mode line.
@end itemize

@node Installation
@section Installation
@enumerate 
@item
@strong{Install Dependencies:} Greader requires a text-to-speech engine
to be installed on your system. You can choose one of the following:

@itemize
@item
@uref{https://github.com/espeak-ng/espeak-ng,eSpeak NG}
@item
@uref{http://devel.freebsoft.org/speechd,Speech Dispatcher}
@item
@uref{https://github.com/rhasspy/piper,Piper}
@end itemize

@item
@strong{Install Greader:} Clone the repository or add it to your Emacs
load path.

@verbatim
(add-to-list 'load-path "/path/to/greader")
(require 'greader)
@end verbatim

@end enumerate

@node Basic Usage
@section Basic Usage
@enumerate 
@item
Start greader mode with @code{M-x greader-mode}.
@item
Press @code{C-r <spc>} to start reading. If desired, you can change the
prefix. See the command @code{greader-set-map-prefix}.
@item
Press @code{<spc>} to stop reading.
@end enumerate

