@node eSpeak / eSpeak NG
@subsection eSpeak / eSpeak NG
The default backend on most systems. Install from your distribution or
from @uref{https://github.com/espeak-ng/espeak-ng,espeak-ng}. No
additional Emacs configuration is required beyond having
@code{espeak-ng} on your @code{PATH}.

@node Speech Dispatcher
@subsection Speech Dispatcher
Middleware layer that can route to many underlying synthesizers. Greader
can start the Speech Dispatcher daemon automatically. See
@uref{http://devel.freebsoft.org/speechd,Speech Dispatcher}.

@node Piper
@subsection Piper
Neural TTS backend that produces high-quality, natural-sounding speech.
Requires two things:

@enumerate 
@item
The @code{piper} binary, available from
@uref{https://github.com/rhasspy/piper,piper} or via your distribution.
@item
The @code{piper.sh} wrapper script shipped with greader. The script must
be executable and accessible on your @code{PATH} or at the path set in
@code{greader-piper-script-path}.
@end enumerate

@multitable @columnfractions 0.33 0.33 0.33 
@headitem 
Variable
 @tab Default
 @tab Description
@item 
@code{greader-piper-script-path}
 @tab @code{piper.sh} in greader directory
 @tab Full path to the @code{piper.sh} wrapper script.
@item 
@code{greader-piper-rate}
 @tab @code{130}
 @tab Speech rate in words per minute.
@end multitable

@verbatim
(setq greader-piper-script-path "/usr/local/bin/piper.sh")
(setq greader-piper-rate 150)
@end verbatim

